Description:
Location, Location, Location
This superb unit is located in one of the best parts of town, within 300 mts of all the amenities Drysdale has to offer.
Comprising of two bedrooms, compact kitchen, and spacious living, separate bathroom, and internal access to the single garage via the laundry.
A private enclosed courtyard at the front with manageable garden space and plenty of room for entertaining.
This property is sure to please the downsizer looking to live closer to central Drysdale, first home buyer wanting to enter the market or investor looking for that property with loads of potential for capital growth as seen so far on the Bellarine.

Description:
Time to make the dream a reality!
Six acres of black cracking soil on Mt Bellarine affords incredible bay and district views and includes four acres under vine.
The gardens surrounding this Tuscan-inspired homestead are superb, exotic and verdant. The paved courtyard with pizza oven and semi commercial kitchen and garage is overseen by glorious palms and exotic trees.
Comprising five bedrooms, three living areas and study, all with beautiful aspects. A combination of architectural features such as French doors, concrete floors, timber lining and lofty ceilings promote space and light. The two bathrooms and kitchen are stylish and modern. Caesar stone tops, handmade cabinetry and quality appliances form the best of the spacious, dining/family area sandwiched between the courtyard and the vineyard. An entertainer’s delight, you will be able to serve your own shiraz, viognier, pinot gris or sauvignon blanc with grapes from your vineyard. These grapes have won gold and silver medals and for what it's worth, we can attest to the fine wine!
Over 70,000 litres of tank water is supplemented by town water. Near new detached double garage/shed plus garage which cleverly can be used as an alfresco area, perfect for cellar door sales and functions.
A unique slice of semi-rural living only half an hour from Geelong, you can live la dolce vita!
For more detailed information on this property SMS '221 WHITCOMBES' to 0428 444 841

Description:
BELLARINE LIFESTYLE ON 2075 SQM., WITH A LEAFY OUTLOOK TO THE BAY.
Loads of space and style, light and bright throughout with excellent proportions, No. 48 provides a lifestyle property within the vibrant village of Drysdale. Gracious tiled entrance, formal dining and lounge room, extra spacious open plan area including gourmet kitchen , informal dining and living, all overlooking the outdoor undercover area for entertaining , powder room and laundry downstairs as well. The wide staircase leads to a big mezzanine level , can be used as rumpus/games room or modified to provide excellent theatre room. The main bedroom is more a retreat room big enough to sit and relax , 2 WIR'S and full ensuite with spa bath, the other three are queensize bedrooms , large bathroom . Features include stone benches, imported chandeliers, stainless steel appliances, gas cooktop, wall oven , walk in pantry, dishwasher, ducted gas heating and evaporative cooling upstairs and downstairs, two split systems, custom fitted outside blinds , loads of storage , quality window furnishings and fittings and more to impress. The orchard, native gardens and winding paths with lawn frame this wonderful home. Double garage (direct internal access), freestanding shed big enough for boat/caravan and.......work area. Within the town area yet a private haven , you must inspect to appreciate.

Description:
Downsize not Compromise
This stylishly renovated front unit is ideally located in close proximity to all of Drysdale’s shops and amenities. The complete renovation throughout includes 5kw Solar Panels with new HWS, a beautiful new kitchen with SS appliances, a thoughtfully designed functional laundry with linen hopper, bathroom with large walk in shower for disabled access, 2 newly carpeted bedrooms with large BIRs and ceiling fans, quality block out blinds, downlights and reverse cycle split system for year round comfort. Outside enjoys a fantastic rear courtyard with pergola, single garage plus car space with side access, BBQ area and a garden shed making this fabulous unit perfect for those wanting to downsize and still enjoy contemporary modern luxuries. There are so many wonderful features in this property that an inspection is a must and will truly delight!

Description:
Sought After Drysdale Unit
Located in Wyndham Mews in the central hub of Drysdale. This flourishing township still retains its country-feel with a beautiful central park and lake area for strolling or sitting outdoors. Central to Geelong and the Bellarine Peninsula these units are in demand.
This immaculate unit comprises spacious rooms through-out with ample storage not found in modern units and is complimented by the convenience of the local shopping centre and all necessary amenities within walking distance. Built with all the finishing touches needed - central heating, evaporative cooling, air conditioner, fans to all rooms, tinted windows, undercover outdoor entertaining area and room to park a second vehicle.
Inspection by appointment with the agent

Description:
Pretty As A Picture
Showcasing a stunning light and bright 'feel' this quality build will feel like home from the moment you turn the key.
• An impressive street scape sets an anticipation for what will be a memorable inspection; I couldn't think of another property in today's market that nails the brief 'nothing to be done'!
• The main living area boasts a lovely northerly orientation and ensures it is bathed in natural light all year round. Expansive glass stacker doors beautifully frame fully landscaped rear gardens and create a seamless inside/outside connection to a beautifully appointed decked alfresco zone – perfect place for an early coffee and/or a glass of your favourite wine at sunset.
• The kitchen 'serves up' a practical user friendly design (complete with expansive walk in pantry) and boasts some luxury features including dual Caesar 200mm stone bench tops, feature pendant lighting and 900ml stainless steel gas cooker.
• A second living area continues the theme of 'light and bright' and provides further conveniences to what is a lovely free flowing floor plan.
• The master bedroom suit is spacious and is complete with an equally generous walk in robe. A trio of floor to ceiling feature windows provide lovely natural light and enhance the neutral tones. The additional bedrooms are generously sized and have built in robes.
• Simply too many additional features to list but here is just a few to wet your appetite; ducted heating, split system cooling, designer ceiling fans, porcelain tiles, double remote controlled garage and quality finishes throughout.
• Central Walk has quickly established itself as Drysdale's exclusive estate. Beautiful wetlands, open tree lined streets and homes stamped with quality as far as the eye can see. This property looks a wonderful home for today and savvy investment for the future.

Description:
Modern Elegance and Grand Scale Luxury Living
This highly appealing newly built home offers a stunning combination of light-filled interiors and impressive quality throughout. The family friendly floor plan is designed for comfort at every turn, making this home one that will be at the top of everyone’s wish list!
On entrance, this light filled sensation features a crisp neutral colour palette throughout, that flows to the hub of the home, an exceptional stylish open plan kitchen, dining and living area that will be a sure talking point amongst buyers.
The dedicated family-sized kitchen with stone bench tops, 900mm oven, dishwasher and an abundance of storage space in your very own butler’s pantry. A designated second living space at the rear of the home adds further family appeal, making a great theatre room, rumpus room or perfect as a kid’s study space. An ideal choice for families, this home makes its quality abundantly clear, both inside and out with stacker sliding doors that open onto a rear entertaining deck area.
Offering four generous sized bedrooms with built in robes and delivering modern master suite luxury with ensuite complete with a large shower and deluxe walk in robe.
The laundry space has external access to the outdoor clothesline and to plenty of back yard space with room for the kids and pets to play. The double garage with remote control includes internal and external access.
Showcasing modern fixtures and fittings throughout, low maintenance landscaped gardens ducted heating and evaporative cooling. Striking modern colours and high ceilings throughout the home complete the inside of this brilliant abode.
Set within the highly regarded estate, nearby beautiful parks and wetlands providing a family friendly setting. With convenience on offer, easy access to some of the best surf coast beaches on the peninsula & just minutes from the local shopping precinct, cafes & shops.
There is no need to worry about building with this truly spectacular family masterpiece offering a superb lifestyle - this slice of paradise won't last long.
Roncon Real Estate – An Agency like no other!

Description:
Best Unit on Barrands
A mere 13 years old this 2 bedroom quiet unit is the best on the block! Freshly painted with a new gas ducted heating unit plus a reverse cycle split system which is just 12 months old. Down lights featuring throughout the large & bright living zone. Lounge has immaculate carpets flowing through to open plan kitchen & dining with stylish floating floors & sliding doors to the backyard. Kitchen has stainless steel appliances including dishwasher & a walk in pantry perfect to store all your groceries. Bedrooms are super spacious & both have big built in robes with the bathroom located perfectly in the middle for easy use. Large single car garage has remote roller door & internal access direct into the laundry. With off street parking for 2 mores cars & the unit is surrounded by low maintenance gardens, all your downsizing boxes will be ticked. Walk only 500 meters to all central Drysdale has to offer cafes, medical facilities, library, post office, supermarkets & shops.

Description:
Attention Lifestyle Buyers
This beautiful property of approximately 14.5 acres is located on the outskirts of the Drysdale township. The expansive rural outlook stretches across paddocks and tree lines to the Port Phillip Heads. Enjoy the established native vegetation which attracts a variety of local bird life. Garden or tinker in the abundant work shop area whilst the Queenscliff - Drysdale steam train chugs leisurely by. The property is adjacent to the Bellarine Rail Trail where you can take advantage of those long bike or pony rides.
The immaculate four bedroom home has been tastefully renovated in a contemporary style that gives the property an easy-living appeal. Living areas are open and inviting with a light and bright northerly aspect. The outdoor entertaining area is a massive family space, fully enclosed with inbuilt barbeque and fans, perfect for those large gatherings. Bedrooms are spacious with ample storage and immaculately presented. Inspection is a must to appreciate the qualities of this immaculately maintained lifestyle property.
Shedding would be suitable for the avid horse owner's stables or a tradesman's storage area. Includes a 9m x 15m zincalume shed with 2 roller doors and concrete flooring, second shedding includes 2 x 6m x 12m, 30,000 litre water tank, small holding paddock at the rear and good quality fencing around the perimeter of the property. Town water is connected.
Inspect by appointment only.
Insights: 180 Andersons Road, Drysdale VIC 3222 was last sold in 2018.

Build your dream home!
Here is a fantastic opportunity to purchase a vacant 775m2 block of land with 20m frontage ideally located within close proximity to the charming town of Drysdale accessed by a private driveway set back off the main road. Description:
Larger Blocks Hard to Find
This rare, titled block is located in the prestigious, boutique estate of Central Walk just a short stroll to shopping, professional offices, child care and cafes. Living in Drysdale and close to the Bellarine is a lifestyle choice not to be missed !
The wide 16 meter frontage and a generous 536m2 will allow plenty of scope for your new build. Ground work to level the block has already been completed. All that is left to do is have the plans drawn !
Properties in this well positioned estate are realising great resale prices as astute purchasers see the benefits of living in this boutique area. Drysdale is less than 30 minutes from Geelong and closer still to the bayside townships, surf beaches, wineries and bay ferries. Drysdale is also well known for its wide choice of educational options for young families.
Contact agent for further information.

Description:
Rustic Charm!
This beautifully appointed residence presents a genuine 'one of a kind' opportunity to secure a quality property with an enviable land holding (545m2) within Drysdale's most sought after estate – Central Walk.
• A striking contemporary build is complimented by a lovely 'rustic' twist! Modern straight architectural lines work seamlessly against the use of recycled timber, the character of reclaimed brick pathways and established native plantations.
• Showcasing a stunning light and bright 'feel' this quality property will feel like home from the moment you turn the key.
• The kitchen 'serves up' a practical user friendly design (complete with expansive walk in pantry) and boasts some luxury features including feature pendant lighting, 900ml gas cooker, stainless steel appliances and an oversized fridge cavity.
• 2 independent living areas provide great scope and flexibility to an already user friendly floor. The main living area offers a seamless connection to a wonderfully private and sheltered alfresco zone.
• The master bedroom is spacious and is complete with an equally generous walk in robe. A glass sliding doors opens out onto a stunning reclaimed brick alfresco flanked by a stunning native plantation; without doubt a lovely private space to take in an early morning coffee.
• All 3 additional bedrooms boast great size, built in robes and courtesy of the generous block a lovely outlook to the landscaped gardens.
• I personally can't think of another property in today's market which offers such a genuine 'turn the key and start enjoying from day 1' – all the hard work is done! Simply too many additional features to list but here is just a few to wet your appetite; ducted heating and cooling, custom window furnishings, rustic garden shed, solar boosted hot water, a water tank complete with a pump and dual pedestrian rear access ensures this property ticks all the boxes.
• Central Walk has quickly established itself as Drysdale's exclusive estate. Beautiful wetlands, open tree lined streets and homes stamped with quality as far as the eye can see. This property looks like a wonderful home for today and savvy investment for the future.
Insights: 30 Stonebridge Road, Drysdale VIC 3222 was last sold in 2018 and 35 other 4 bedroom house in Drysdale have recently been sold.

Description:
Stylish and Contemporary
Stylish and sleek contemporary design come to the fore with this stunning 'as new' 4 bedroom residence. Showcasing a free flowing floor plan and boasting a beautifully light and bright 'feel' this prize property will appeal to purchasers with an eye for detail.
• Generous proportions throughout endorse this fine properties appeal to a broad buying bench; a great family home with independent living zones or the perfect downsizer with a low maintenance profile.
• The hub of the home is a beautifully appointed kitchen, expansive dual stone benchtops, 900mm gas cook top, tiled splash back, stainless steel appliances and an oversized walk in pantry nail the brief of a stylish yet functional working space. A warm and welcoming relaxed family living area is bathed in natural light and is cleverly oriented with an outlook to a secure rear yard.
• A 2nd independent living area is generous and provides further flexibility to an already user friendly floor plan
• The master bedroom with its northerly aspect soaks up lovely filtered light; a sun bed window feature, spacious ensuite with oversized luxury shower and a walk in robe complete the picture.
• All 3 additional bedrooms have built in robes
• A custom built hard wood decked alfresco is eye catching and it provides a great area to host a BBQ with family and friends
• All the modern comforts and inclusions create a genuine 'turn the key' and start enjoying from day 1 prospect; ducted heating, multiple ceiling fans, high ceilings, double remote controlled garage, exposed aggregate driveway and an established lawn.

Solid Home Built to Last
Centrally located and solidly constructed by a local tradesman this three bedroom home with two living areas would suit the young family or retiree. The master bedroom has a wall of BIRs and access to the two-way bathroom.
Second living area incorporates a spacious kitchen with plenty of cupboard space and access to the side yard and patio for outdoor entertaining. Bedrooms 2 & 3 are located at the rear of the home. A spacious carport and back yard with room to move complete this attractive 683m2 property.
